HEADWORD: Autonomasy
<hw>Au`to*nom"a*sy</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Auto-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a name, fr. <?/ a name; or for E.
<ets>antonomasia</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>The use of a word
of common or general signification for the name of a particular thing;
<as>as, ⟦ldquo⟧He has gone to <ex>town</ex>,⟦rdquo⟧ for, ⟦ldquo⟧He has
gone to <ex>London</ex>.⟦rdquo⟧</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Autonomic</ent>⟦br⟧
